The following is a transcript of a series of logs detailing conversations between wanderer '''Gabriel Nelson''' and a suspected '''Poltergeist''' hosting a radio as means of communication. '''Gabriel Nelson''' had been a new wanderer, and after being stranded, used a radio to try and communicate, which was presumably possessed by his '''Poltergeist'''. Said logs took place in [[Level 9]], hiding away from entities in a basement within a small house, reportedly starving during the events of the logs.
-------------------------------
<center>'''LOG 1'''</center><br>

<center>''static hums faintly''</center><br>

[[File:Darkradio.png|center|350px|link= ]]<br>

'''G''': Hello? …Hello? This thing even working? I'm searching for any entrances to [[Level 4]], the closest safe level near me. T-that is what I was told. Is anyone-<br>

<center>''sharp click''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...h-hello?<br>

'''G''': ...What?<br>

<center>''silence stretches''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Gabriel.<br>

'''G''': How do you-<br>

'''G''': Okay, n-not funny. Who is this?<br>

<center>''silence lingers''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': GabrielGabrielGabrielGabriel-

'''G''': Stop—HEY, STOP-<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': GabrielGabrielGabriel-<br>

<center>''A thud is heard nearby.''</center><br>

'''G''': Wh..?

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ''giggling''<br>

<center>''A table drags slowly across the floor.''</center><br>

'''G''': Did you just... move that desk?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ..<br>

'''G''': ...hello?

<center>''The same desk violently scrapes again.''</center><br>

'''G''': OKAY—OKAY... WHO ARE YOU!?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': I'm... funny...<br>

<center>''Gabriel attempted to readjust the radio.''</center><br>

'''G''': Hello? Hello!? Can anyone hear me?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Yes! Of course!<br>
--------------------
*Note: The Poltergeist appears to change voices while talking through the radio, switching between the tones of an adult, a child, a woman, and many others.
--------------------
<center>'''LOG 2'''</center><br>

[[File:Basementthing.jpg|center|350px|link= ]]<br>

'''G''': What are you?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': …<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Yours.<br>

'''G''': That doesn’t answer anything.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Mine too.<br>

'''G''': What the fuck is that supposed to mean?<br>

<center>''radio goes completely silent''</center><br>

'''G''': Hey-HEY-<br>

<center>''sudden distorted scream through radio''</center><br>

'''G''': JESUS-!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': HAHAHAHAHAHA-<br>

<center>''laughter cuts off instantly''</center><br>
--------------------
*Note: The voices and sounds the '''Poltergeist''' make appear to be taken from memories belonging to its host.
*Note: Gabriel refused to engage further with the Suspected Poltergeist for the remainder of the day after Log 2.
--------------------
<center>'''LOG 3'''</center><br>

[[File:Flashbulb.webp|center|350px|link= ]]<br>

'''G''': ...Hey. Are you there?<br>

<center>''No response.''</center><br>

'''G''': Ohoho, so now, you're silent huh? You've done nothing but be a nuisance to me the past 2 days, and now you're silent?!

<center>''...''</center><br>

'''G''': You fucking bastard.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ''imitating'' You fucking bastard.<br>

'''G''': Don't start with your bullshit again.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Don't start with your bulls-<br>

<center>''Gabriel grabbed the radio and slammed it against the wall. Somehow, it didn't break. The radio fell to the floor.''</center><br>

'''G:''' YOU COWARD! WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU SUPPOSED TO BE!? A FUCKING DEMON!? WHY DO YOU DO THIS?! WHY THE HELL ARE YOU HERE!? I'VE HAD NOBODY ELSE TO TALK TO SINCE I'VE ARRIVED HERE, BUT YOU. YOU, OF ALL POSSIBLE!-<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Because... it's fun.<br>

'''G''': ...<br>

'''G''': ...That is your answer?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Did I... stutter?<br>

<center>''A creaking door was heard in the upper floor.''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': You are... too loud. Loud loud loud loud loud loud-<br>

'''G''': ''sniffling'' Please... stop... just stop..<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Your noise... '''it brought one of them over.''' You should hide. Hide hide hide hide hide-

<center>''A strange voice, presumed to originate from a [[Entity 3|hostile entity]] was heard in the background.''</center><br>

'''G''': ...W-what was that? Is that you again?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Hide hide hide hide hide hide hide hide<br>

<center>''Hesitating, Gabriel hid behind the table that had been dragged back in Log 1. However, the Smiler had already sensed him. The smiler broke into the basement, quickly rushing towards its prey.''</center><br>

'''G''': '''AAAAAAHHHH!!'''-<br>

<center>''Suddenly, a blinding flash of light engulfed the attic from the lightbulb, which had been turned off for days. The smiler wailed, quickly disappearing away out of the attic.''</center><br>

<center>''The blind light had been so intense Gabriel fainted under the shock of the encounter and the flash, passing out in the attic.''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Loud... loud... loud... loud...<br>
--------------------
*Note: Following Log 3, Gabriel was passed out for approximately 16 hours. The suspected Poltergeist had repeated the same words for over 12 hours total before going silent, presumably to avoid bringing any more attention.
*Note: Suspected Poltergeist appears to be chaotic albeit possessing a sense of caution and protectiveness over its wanderer, thus why it supposedly saved Gabriel from a smiler attack.
--------------------
<center>'''LOG 4'''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Wake up, Gabriel<br>

<center>''...''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Wake up wake up wake up wake up wake up wake up wake-<br>

'''G''': Hngh...! ''deep breathing'' ...what... did you do?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Save... your life.<br>

'''G''': ''cough'' Oh, so now you're nice, huh? How do I know you didn't send that thing after me? How do I know this isn't just... one of the many traps I've fallen through?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': HA... ...haha...<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': If I wanted you gone... you wouldn't have woken up.<br>

'''G''': Then why am I still here?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...because you’re interesting.<br>

'''G''': You think this is funny?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...yes.<br>

<center>''faint creaking echoes from above''</center><br>

'''G''': You... You keep talking like you know everything! Like you’ve been watching me.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...not everything. just enough.<br>

'''G''': Enough for what?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...to follow.<br>

'''G''': Follow?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...to wake.<br>

'''G''': That doesn’t mean anything! Did '''you''' bring me here!?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': You came here, then I did.<br>

'''G''': Are you implying that you’re tied to me?<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': We overlap.<br>

'''G''': That’s not comforting.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': This whole time... you've been the one asking questions. The one drowned in confusion... mystery. It feeds me.<br>

<center>''radio emits a faint, uneven hum''</center><br>

'''G''': You didn't answer my question. Did you bring me here?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...no...yes.<br>

'''G''': Which one is it?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': You asked the wrong question.<br>

'''G''': Then what’s the right one?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': '''Why are you still here?'''<br>

'''G''': …<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': You stayed.<br>

'''G''': I didn’t have a choice, and you know that! Anywhere I go, is a death sentence. Don't try to flip the role on me.<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...<br>

<center>''radio crackles; heat distortion faintly audible''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': …they’re coming again.<br>

'''G''': What?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Not yet. soon.<br>

'''G''': Then help me! For once, actually help me!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': ...listen.<br>

'''G''': To what?!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Not me.<br>

<center>''radio begins overheating; static intensifies''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': There’s a way out. You’ll hear it. but not out of this realm. It's your home now. '''Our''' home.<br>

'''G''': I don’t understand!<br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': Then you will.<br>

<center>''long pause; static drops to near silence''</center><br>

'''Suspected Poltergeist''': If we will ever meet again... your choices after this will determine.<br>

<center>''The table scrapes across the floor one last time. The radio abruptly cools as the presence leaves it.''</center><br>

'''G''': You…<br>

'''Radio Speaker''': Hello? Anyone there? W-we got your message at [[Level 4]].<br>

'''G''': Y-yes, yes, I can hear you! Please, I'm in some sort of suburb... I can't survive much longer; those smiling monsters are outside. Please, if you know any path I can take... I'll take it. I don't care whatever risk…<br>
--------------------
*Note: Log 4 proves that Poltergeists may be able of advanced knowledge that we have yet to comprehend fully, but no further progress beyond this conversation has been discovered.
*Note: The radio's state implies Poltergeists may cause technological appliances to overheat when hosted for too long, thus why it had to leave to prevent it from being destroyed.
--------------------
Following these logs, Gabriel Nelson was successfully evacuated to Level 4. He had suffered severe psychological trauma, starvation, and exhaustion. Afterwards, Gabriel affirmed he had tried to communicate with the Suspected Poltergeist many times after and even tried using radios to speak to it again. However, none of these attempts have been successful. Regardless, the information gathered from these logs was crucial in further understanding the biology and intelligence of Poltergeists, and Gabriel's Poltergeist appears to be more talkative than other Poltergeists, making this among the more unique cases of Poltergeist encounters.
