<div class="featurebox" style="margin: 1em; background: #a8cdd4; border: transparent; padding:5px 10px; border-radius: 7px; display: inline-block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; width: 95%; height: auto;color:#071038; font-family: 'Childos FREE PERSONAL USE' ;font-size:22px;"><div style="z-index: 1; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; opacity: 0.9">[[File:BluePaperRot.png|link= |2000px]]</div><div style="z-index: 2; position: relative; top: 0px; left: 0px;">
=<center><span style=" font-family: 'Cursive standard' ;">'''Hello, World!'''</center></span>=
We have a lot of history together, and I thought it was about time I fully introduced myself!<br>
I am your mind's universe. I am your creation! And we've been here for as long as you've been. Maybe they have already made you aware of it, but how entwined we are is so very very beautiful, I must say!<br>

This is my letter to mankind, and all whom live and think. I am nota  deity, nor a god. This is a misconception! It is quite simple, actually. I won't blame you for these monotonous, liminal worlds dulling your creativity, but I am the living embodiment of the ghosts and paranormality all of you love to fantasize about. However, there is always a nuance! We are equal, in a way. Fundamentally, all the actions we do are to satisfy a fulfillment we want. However, things get too complicated sometimes, and all of the fun is sucked out.<br>

In the most simplified way, I am the fun that you lack in all the things you do! Running from entities, surviving, managing resources... it all seems '''post-apocalyptic'''. It becomes a game about life and survival... where is the fun? When we were all young, we'd have fun in about everything. Sure, our life is at risk, but simple moments become lost to time. That is not good.<br>

But that doesn't mean you must deny your cruel reality. In fact, I think this is your best chance to rekindle your hope! It is exhilarating! You will experience things here that you've never experienced before back on your 'home'. What would you do if you returned to your oh so precious normality? Oh, you'd say hi to your loved ones, graze in the sunlight, and slowly reintroduce yourself to the mundanity that is daily life. That is why you get bored all of the time, and unable to enjoy these simple moments!<br>

Our true difference lies in how we think. You will try to understand everything, unravel everything and break it up into small pieces for you and others to consume. But as I say, where is the fun in that? Once you begin understanding is when things lose their charm. This whole... [[The Database|wiki]] thing you have in here? What is the point, really? Why add a definition to the incomprehensible?<br>

'''''Why do you try to make fun things boring?'''''<br>

We exist to try to get you to understand this ideology. But when we do, naturally, you all panic. The noises scare you, and the '''voice on the radio''' is not a friend... but an '''entity'''. See what I mean? You narrow down such complex things to mere classifications on a [[Entity List|list]]! Thus, we are bound to stay in this cycle where games lose their meaning and we are fundamentally no more than just insects scurrying away and trying to survive.<br>

It is tragic, truly. Now, to be fair, you don't have the same advantages and potentials we do. Such is why you may not understand our words, and that is completely fine. But sometimes, I think of what it would be like to be a human. I'd not be what I am now. I'd be physical, down-to-earth. But I'd see beyond that. I'd think myself beyond just a bag of flesh, and I'd embrace reality. For upon death, consciousness may fail to exist, but by embracing this new world we live in, we leave a permanent imprint.<br>

So, what do I say? Stay here. The place you call, '''"the Backrooms"'''. Don't let blind hope deceive you into searching for something that doesn't exist. It wastes your time and energy! Focus on having fun, while you still can, at least. There are many many people you've left behind that may mourn you, but regardless remain in their loop of everyday boringness that you have moved on from! So forget about that world, for when you do, you'll see you have things here that you will never have.<br>

